== Roasted Chickpeas ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g carton} in a #sieve{}, then pat dry with #kitchen paper{}. Spread the chickpeas onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{for roasting} and sprinkle over the @curry powder mix{1%sachet}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss to coat evenly. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until crispy, ~{16-18%minutes}. Carefully remove from the oven and turn halfway through.

Pop the @garlic clove{2}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{for roasting} and scrunch to enclose it. Roast the parcel until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Croutons and Chicken ==

Meanwhile, tear the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks.

Pop the ciabatta onto a baking tray in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{for croutons}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat well.

Bake the croutons on the middle shelf until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}, then remove from the oven and set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{for frying} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Once cooked, set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Green Beans ==

While everything bakes, trim the @green beans{80%g} and cut into thirds.

Put the chicken pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{for stir-fry}. Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn the heat down to medium, then add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some foil.

Cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat.

== Mango Chutney Yoghurt Dressing ==

Once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the mashed garlic, @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}, @mango chutney{40%g}, @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and toss through the dressing. Set aside to macerate.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, add the chicken, croutons, roasted chickpeas, green beans, tomatoes and @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the dressing. Toss to evenly coat.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

Share the salad between your #serving bowls{}.

Crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} to finish. Enjoy!